Chapter 3: Map the Institution Network
Core Question
Which institutions already hold trust, space, memory, or influence?
Understand
An ecosystem is not built by individuals alone.
Institutions hold memory and structure.
A society should know the institutions around it:
Churches
 Schools
 Barbershops and salons
 Fraternities and sororities
 Lodges
 Neighborhood associations
 Local nonprofits
 Business associations
 Cultural spaces
 Mutual aid groups
 Senior centers
 Youth organizations
 Clinics
 Legal aid groups
 Food pantries
 Libraries
 Community centers
 Local media
 Credit unions
 Reentry groups
 Tenant associations
 Parent groups
Some institutions may become partners.
Some may become anchors.
Some may be inactive but still trusted.
Some may hold buildings.
Some may hold history.
Some may reach people the society cannot reach alone.
The goal is not to use institutions.
The goal is to understand the ecosystem and build respectful relationships.
Discuss
Which institutions do people already trust?
Which institutions have space?
Which institutions have records, history, or elders?
Which institutions reach youth?
Which institutions reach families in crisis?
Which institutions should we approach carefully?
