Chapter 4: Map Risks and Threats
Core Question
What could weaken or extract from the ecosystem?
Understand
An ecosystem must be protected.
Growth creates visibility.
Visibility can attract support, but it can also attract extraction.
The society should name risks early.
Risks may include:
Gentrification
 Property tax pressure
 Predatory lending
 Business displacement
 Burnout
 Founder-dependence
 Data misuse
 Public exposure of hardship
 Political manipulation
 Grant dependency
 Mission drift
 Partnership extraction
 Youth exploitation
 Elder neglect
 Conflict without repair
 Money confusion
 Unclear ownership
 Digital platform dependence
 Disaster vulnerability
 Legal confusion
Protection begins with naming.
If the society knows the risks, it can build standards before pressure arrives.
Discuss
What is already extracting from this community?
What risks grow as we become more visible?
What risks grow if money increases?
What risks grow if we partner with outside organizations?
What risks grow if property becomes involved?
What risks grow if youth or elder information is mishandled?
