PART TWO: CONNECT THE ECOSYSTEM

Chapter 5: Choose an Ecosystem Pathway
Core Question
Which part of the ecosystem should we strengthen first?
Understand
The society cannot strengthen the whole ecosystem at once.
It must choose one pathway.
Choose based on:
Evidence
 Capacity
 Urgency
 Solvability
 Trust
 Existing relationships
 Available leadership
 Risk
 Alignment with purpose
Possible ecosystem pathways:
Business circulation
 Property stewardship
 Youth formation
 Preparedness network
 Elder care and memory
 Culture and creator ownership
 Institutional partnerships
 Buying club
 Shared services
 Care infrastructure
 Local media and narrative
 Skills and training network
The society should not choose the most impressive pathway.
It should choose the pathway with the best mix of need, readiness, and responsibility.
Discuss
What did our maps reveal?
Which pathway connects to the most urgent repeated need?
Which pathway uses assets we already have?
Which pathway has leadership ready?
Which pathway is too risky right now?
Which pathway would strengthen the whole society?
Build: Ecosystem Pathway Selection
Pathway selected:

Why this pathway?

Evidence from maps:

Existing assets connected:

Risks:

Leader or liaison:

What we are not doing yet:

Success measure:

