Chapter 7: Create the Circulation Plan
Core Question
How will value move through the ecosystem on purpose?
Understand
Circulation means value moves through trusted routes instead of disappearing immediately.
Value is not only money.
Value includes:
Money
 Time
 Labor
 Skills
 Knowledge
 Attention
 Space
 Tools
 Relationships
 Culture
 Youth opportunity
 Elder memory
 Preparedness resources
A circulation plan shows:
What moves
 From whom
 To whom
 Through what structure
 How often
 With what record
 Toward what goal
Without a circulation plan, support stays scattered.
With a circulation plan, the society can turn care, spending, skills, and attention into power.
Discuss
What value are we trying to move?
Who has it?
Who needs it?
What route should it take?
How will we record it?
How will we know it strengthened the ecosystem?
Build: Circulation Plan
Value being circulated:
Money / Skills / Labor / Time / Knowledge / Attention / Space / Tools / Culture / Other
