PART THREE: BUILD ECOSYSTEM PROJECTS

Chapter 9: Business Circulation Project
Core Question
Can we organize customers, not just cheer for businesses?
Understand
A business cannot survive on applause.
It needs customers, referrals, repeat buyers, useful feedback, and predictable support.
The society can support business circulation through:
Buying campaigns
 Member purchasing commitments
 Institutional purchasing
 Business directory updates
 Vendor referrals
 Youth apprenticeships
 Shared services
 Emergency business support
 Skill workshops
 Cooperative marketing
Business support must be transparent.
Avoid favoritism.
Disclose relationships.
Define criteria.
Report results.
The goal is not to make one business popular for a week.
The goal is to build a route where money, trust, and customers circulate more intentionally.
Discuss
Which businesses meet recurring community needs?
Which businesses are trusted?
Which businesses need organized customers?
What can members actually buy consistently?
What relationship disclosures are needed?
How will the campaign report results?
