Chapter 10: Property Stewardship Project
Core Question
Can we protect land, homes, buildings, and documents before crisis?
Understand
Property stewardship begins before purchase.
A community may already have homes, church buildings, land, family property, rental units, business spaces, or vacant parcels connected to its people.
These assets can be lost through:
Unpaid taxes
 Heirs property confusion
 No will or estate plan
 Missing documents
 Predatory offers
 Insurance gaps
 Deferred maintenance
 Development pressure
 Family conflict
 Unclear ownership
 Lack of trusted guidance
The society’s first property project should protect, educate, organize documents, and connect people to qualified help when needed.
Do not expose sensitive property details.
Property work requires privacy, patience, and stewardship.
Discuss
What property risks are repeating?
What documents do families struggle to find?
What can be taught safely?
What requires professional help?
Who should serve as Property Liaison?
How will privacy be protected?
Build: Property Stewardship Project
