Chapter 11: Youth Pipeline Project
Core Question
Can youth move from attendance to responsibility?
Understand
A youth pipeline is more than a youth event.
It is a path from exposure to practice to responsibility.
Youth should be able to learn:
History
 Bookkeeping
 Technology
 Meeting facilitation
 Business skills
 Property stewardship
 Preparedness
 Media
 Research
 Care work
 Project reporting
 Governance basics
The society should create real roles with safe support.
A youth pipeline may include:
Mentorship
 Apprenticeship
 Youth ledger assistant
 History archive project
 Preparedness captain
 Business campaign assistant
 Media/documentation team
 Meeting support role
 Youth opportunity fund
 Skill workshop series
The goal is not to entertain youth.
The goal is to form future stewards.
Discuss
What youth are already connected?
What skills should they learn?
What role can be real but safe?
Who can mentor consistently?
What output should youth complete?
How will youth report what they learned?
