PART FOUR: PROTECT AND REPORT THE ECOSYSTEM

Chapter 14: Ecosystem Standards
Core Question
What standards protect the ecosystem from confusion and extraction?
Understand
Ecosystem work creates more relationships.
More relationships create more risk.
The society needs standards before the work grows.
Standards should cover:
Money transparency
 Privacy
 Conflict of interest
 Business support criteria
 Property confidentiality
 Youth safety
 Elder dignity
 Partnership approval
 Public communication
 Data protection
 Cultural consent
 Reporting
 Decision-making
 Exit rules
Standards do not slow the work.
They protect it from harm.
If a business is supported, disclose relationships.
If a property issue is discussed, protect details.
If youth are involved, use extra care.
If a partner wants data, ask why.
If culture is shared publicly, obtain consent.
If money moves, record it.
If the society speaks publicly, approve the message.
Discuss
Where could confusion happen?
Where could favoritism appear?
Where could privacy be harmed?
Where could culture be extracted?
Where could youth or elders be exposed?
What standard must be written now?
