Chapter 15: Ecosystem Dashboard
Core Question
How do we see whether the ecosystem is becoming stronger?
Understand
An ecosystem needs a dashboard.
Not only for activity.
For health.
The dashboard should show:
Money circulation
 Businesses supported
 Needs addressed
 Care team activity
 Youth engaged
 Elders supported
 Property projects
 Preparedness actions
 Skills/assets activated
 Institutions connected
 Partnerships active
 Reports completed
 Risks identified
 Standards updated
 Next action
The dashboard helps the society see whether the ecosystem is getting stronger or simply busier.
Busyness is not the goal.
Durability, circulation, protection, and capacity are the goal.
Discuss
What should we measure?
What should we not over-measure?
What numbers matter?
What stories matter?
What would show that the ecosystem is healthier?
What would warn us that we are scattering?
