Chapter 16: Ecosystem Report
Core Question
What circulated, what stayed, what grew, and what needs repair?
Understand
The Ecosystem Report turns scattered activity into shared memory.
The report should answer:
What did we map?
What did we connect?
What value circulated?
What stayed in the community longer?
What businesses were supported?
What property was protected?
What youth were trained?
What elders were honored?
What preparedness improved?
What institutions were connected?
What risks appeared?
What standards were strengthened?
What should we build next?
A truthful ecosystem report is more useful than an impressive one.
The goal is not to claim transformation too early.
The goal is to show evidence of stronger circulation, stronger protection, and stronger connection.
Discuss
What circulated?
What stayed?
What grew?
What became more protected?
What became more connected?
What needs repair?
What should be the next ecosystem pathway?
