Closing Principle
A community does not become wealthy because one business opens.
A community becomes stronger when trust creates relationships, relationships create mutual aid, mutual aid creates organization, organization creates institutions, and institutions create the soil where businesses, property, culture, youth, preparedness, and power can grow.
The Ecosystem Container is about building that soil.
Not everything at once.
Not activity for its own sake.
Not visibility without structure.
The work is to connect what has been scattered.
To protect what has been vulnerable.
To circulate what has been leaving.
To train who will inherit it.
To report what has been built.
Prosperity is an ecosystem.
Build the soil.

